summary: Have I Got Whos For You (Winter Warmer Edition)
title: Have I Got Whos For You (Winter Warmer Edition)
body:
Have I Got Whos For You (Winter Warmer Edition)

I mean, I made this one weeks ago, the last time it happened, but it seems fairly topical right now.

You have to feel a little bit sorry for Theresa May. She inherited an absolute dog’s breakfast, a situation that no one was going to be able to resolve because the concept of government in this country (and, indeed, in many democracies) is far more about the acquisition of power than it is about…

summary: This one feels like bit of a turning point in the shading area. I tried blending a bit more in this drawing, and I think it...
caption:
This one feels like bit of a turning point in the shading area. I tried blending a bit more in this drawing, and I think it really helped add something to defining the shapes/lighting in the image. It kind of falls over in the stubble area, and the head’s on at the wrong angle (which caused all kinds of issues with the eyebrows), but I reckon if you squint you can tell who it’s meant to be. The title might be a giveaway too! … maybe the tags as well.

Will need to work on hair soon, it’s becoming a sticking point.
